      <h2>What You Need to Know About Driving License Conversion</h2>

      <h3>The Real Question: Can I Convert My License Directly?</h3>
      <p>The UAE maintains a list of approved countries whose driving licenses can be converted without taking a driving test. If your country is on this list, conversion is straightforward: translate your license, pass an eye test, complete the paperwork, and receive your UAE license.</p>

      <p>If your country is not on the approved list, you will need to take driving lessons at an RTA-approved school and pass the UAE driving test. The translated license is still required for your file opening.</p>

      <h3>Approved Countries for Direct Conversion</h3>
      <p>The RTA allows direct license conversion for holders of licenses from these countries:</p>

      <div class="country-grid">
        <div class="country-group">
          <h4>GCC Countries</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Saudi Arabia</li>
            <li>Kuwait</li>
            <li>Bahrain</li>
            <li>Oman</li>
            <li>Qatar</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="country-group">
